Premier of KwaZulu-Natal, Sihle Zikalala briefs the media on the current status and relief efforts in the province. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal Premier, Sihle Zikalala, says they will ask the government to declare the floods a national disaster. Zikalala says the floods have caused greater levels of devastation and that much more assistance will be required to assist those affected. READ: KZN flood death toll rises to 443 He also says that the needs identified are enormous, and billions will be required to repair and rebuild this province. The premier confirmed that death toll from the floods now stands at 443. While, 63 more people are still missing. KwaZulu-Natal Premier, Sihle Zikalala, says they'll ask government to declare the floods a national disaster. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/3e61uzEmDO